c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.0cba88c8-6a10-4a43-8cd8-e919ec99af9c.description=
Sends a command to the telnet server. This should be preceded by Send Username and Send password in a telnet sequence.  The last command in the sequence should have ICT_lastInSession set to true to close the session.  This operation is not the preferred way to use telnet, JRAS Telnet Shell is.

Inputs\:
Command - The command to execute on the remote host.
ICT_Host - The host to execute the command on.
ICT_Port - The port telnet is running on.
ICT_Session - A unique name for the telnet session this command is run from.
ICT_WaitMode - How to wait for the response\: ''none'' - do not wait, ''any'' - wait for any response, ''match'' - wait for response to match the regular expression. Defaults to none.
ICT_TermExpr - The expression to match the server's response before sending the command.
ICT_LastInSession - If set to ''true'', this is deemed the last operation in the session. The session is terminated and removed from the context after this operation finishes.
ICT_Charset - The encoding used for the received characters (for instance ''MS932'' for Japanese Windows). Defaults to UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - Operation succeeded.
failure - Operation failed.

Returns - The standard output of the telnet command.

Authentication Note\:
Send Username and Send Password should preceded this operation to successfully establish a session.
c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.188b805a-7722-4c34-9be0-ded43cca5676.description=
Tries to make a connection to the request port.

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the target host
port - port to connect to
portType - the type of port (TCP or UDP) 

Responses\:
port opened - a successful connection was made
port closed - unable to make a connection
host not found - could not resolve hostname to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
addresses - list of addresses returned from DNS
aliases - list of aliases returned from DNS
addresspinged - actual IP address pinged

c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.59f441e1-0386-46b8-9b2c-26df90d9adb2.description=
Sends a username to the telnet server.  This should be the first operation in a telnet sequence and should be used to establish the telnet session.  It should be configured to wait for the telnet server to emit a login prompt prior to sending the username.

Inputs\:
Username - The username to send to the remote host.
ICT_Host - The host to execute the command on.
ICT_Port - The port telnet is running on.
ICT_Session - A unique name for the telnet session this command is run from.
ICT_UserWaitMode - How to wait for the response\: ''none'' - do not wait, ''any'' - wait for any response, ''match'' - wait for response to match the regular expression. Defaults to none. Should be "match" to wait for a login prompt.
ICT_UserTermExpr - The expression to match the server's response before sending the command. This should match the login prompt of the target server.
ICT_LastInSession - If set to ''true'', this is deemed the last operation in the session. The session is terminated and removed from the context after this operation finishes. This should typically be false for Send Username.
ICT_Charset - The encoding used for the received characters (for instance ''MS932'' for Japanese Windows). Defaults to UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - Operation succeeded.
failure - Operation failed.

Returns - The standard output of the telnet command.

Authentication Note\:
By default this operation expects a "Login\: " or "login\: " prompt.  If the target system has a different login prompt this operation will need to be copied and modified to expect the appropriate login prompt.  After copying this operation to a writable folder, modify the regular expression in the "ICT_UserTermExpr" input that will match the login prompt on the target system.
c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.a29fec43-9e5c-4b49-beb6-b7d94767cfc8.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.

c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.e7bf151f-de31-4031-b226-f6b0a30583c0.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.

c6a4bad7-0554-4dd8-9339-9058c258ea23.ee06bd1a-4734-45de-9446-a4eeeaed4cfa.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.
